1
00:00:00,918 --> 00:00:02,425
Here, there are graves

2
00:00:04,693 --> 00:00:08,540
I told you before, here is the grave of Dr. Patrick Jakhmashian

3
00:00:09,353 --> 00:00:13,279
He was the head of the Armenian community in Mosul

4
00:00:14,297 --> 00:00:18,495
And his brother Joseph Jakhmashian, and the priest

5
00:00:22,182 --> 00:00:23,808
Our priest is buried here

6
00:00:27,134 --> 00:00:33,325
And here there are one, two, three, four, five, six graves, all of them

7
00:00:35,290 --> 00:00:39,033
And three or four graves over there, in that direction

8
00:00:41,949 --> 00:00:44,902
They vandalized all of them, and the writing on them was in Armenian

9
00:00:46,281 --> 00:00:48,726
They removed them all, they left nothing

10
00:00:49,061 --> 00:00:53,560
Only here, there are a few words that are unclear

11
00:00:57,083 --> 00:01:00,736
All the graves had Armenian writing and dates on them

12
00:01:01,176 --> 00:01:02,222
Only this is left

13
00:01:04,645 --> 00:01:08,600
Interviewer: Mr. Abu Ari, tell us, when were these graves established?

14
00:01:08,644 --> 00:01:13,359
They are very old, they existed before I was born, I do not remember

15
00:01:13,429 --> 00:01:14,695
Interviewer: You do not remember? Witness: No

16
00:01:16,947 --> 00:01:20,053
Interviewer: Why have the graves become like this now?

17
00:01:21,718 --> 00:01:22,758
Because of the vandals

18
00:01:25,180 --> 00:01:26,506
Interviewer: Whom do you mean by vandals?

19
00:01:32,515 --> 00:01:35,441
The vandals, I do not know what to tell you

20
00:01:36,199 --> 00:01:39,765
Interviewer: Is this whole place graves?

21
00:01:41,324 --> 00:01:46,384
Starting from here, one, two, three, four, five

22
00:01:47,016 --> 00:01:48,220
These are their graves
